ing Meeting Room rental enquiries for management approvalAssisting and instructing customers in the use of library applications and equipment (self-serve machines, computers, photocopiers, Makerspace equipment etc.)Assisting Assistant Manager to perform troubleshooting of equipment. Ensures equipment is well functioning and has the necessary supplies, notifying management of the need to repair and to order additional supplies.Assists Assistant Managers or Managers with the daily branch operation as required. Typical duties may include but not limited to:Opening and closing the library building Accessing the safeMonitoring appropriate staffing coverage for serviceReporting building related issues or health and safety incidentsResponding to emergency situations as necessarySupports the Customer Experience Team in delivering exceptional service to library customersOperates under the supervision of an assistant manager, who may oversee their work either on-site or from other locationsProvides job shadowing to colleagues as neededFollows established procedures and guidelines for Health and Safety, and Customer Experience functionsEducation and ExperienceLibrary Technician Diploma requiredEarly Childhood Education, Adult Education, or other related courses considered an asset A minimum of two years of recent relevant experienceRequired Skills/KnowledgeAbility to work effectively and collaboratively in a team environmentCommitment to excellent customer serviceDemonstrated effective written and oral communications skillsGood interpersonal skillsExhibited strong problem-solving skillsDemonstrated ability to perform detail oriented tasks, follow direction and proceduresDemonstrated knowledge and ability to complete cataloguing activitiesAbility to work flexible hoursRichmond Hill Public Library ValuesAccessibilityAccountabilityDiversityInnovationIntellectual FreedomLiteracy and Lifelong LearningRespectAbout Richmond Hill Public LibraryRichmond Hill Public Library is committed to inclusive, barrier-free recruitment and selection processes. If contacted to participate in the recruitment and selection process, please advise Human Resources if you require an accommodation.This position may be relocated to another location in the future to meet service needs for the community. All applicants should understand that the ability to work at any library location is a requirement of this position.The Library will require a current Vulnerable Sector Screening from the successful applicant as a condition of employment.Attention Internal Candidates: All current City of Richmond Hill employees are required to apply via the ‘View Jobs for Current Employees’ link on the City’s Careers Page. Compensation 31.82-37.82 Closes: 19 June, 2024 City of Richmond Hill Richmond Hill , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
