Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Director of Human Resources Kelowna , BC Description Director of Human Resources Permanent Full-Time (1.0 FTE / 35 hours weekly) Okanagan Regional Library Headquarters location (Kelowna BC) We are excited to announce the recruitment for a new Director of Human Resources to join our organization and invite qualified candidates to bring their expertise and commitment to service excellence to a role where they can make a real difference. About the Okanagan Regional Library (ORL) The Okanagan Regional Library (ORL) is the 16th largest library in Canada, with approximately 300 employees, serving over 400,000 residents within the Okanagan and Columbia Shuswap region of British Columbia, through 30 locations and on-line services. ORL is currently seeking a Director, Human Resources as a member of its senior management team. The Opportunity The Director, Human Resources is responsible for all aspects of the HR function including recommending, influencing, and implementing the organization’s human resource strategy and organizational development with the aim of enlivening the ORL’s organizational mission, vision, and values. The Director, HR leads a small team providing full-service recruitment and staffing, compensation and benefits administration, management advisory services, labour and employee relations, training and development, occupational health and safety and wellness initiatives within a multi-union, multi-location environment. In addition, the Director provides counsel, development, and support to the management team. A person of integrity and self-direction, the Director will be able to relate to employees and managers at all levels of the organization. Approachable, open, respectful, focused, the Director will bring strong communication, problem-solving, decision-making, project management, and organizational skills to the challenges at hand. Salary shall be determined commensurate with experience within a range of $120,000 to $140,000. In addition, this position provides the successful candidate with a competitive benefits, vacation, and pension arrangements. Education The successful candidate will have a relevant university degree and a minimum of five (5) years. Related Experience Five (5) years of HR experience in a complex union environment, with at least 2 of those years in a leadership role. Experience with public libraries or non-profit organizations is an asset. Experience leading multi-locational organizations is also an asset. Other Requirements In-depth knowledge of relevant legislation and regulations. Ability to interpret and administer collective agreements and employment contracts. Computer literacy in Microsoft Office and HR-related applications Participates in continued education and ensures skills and knowledge are up to date. The primary work locations is at the ORL headquarters but the incumbent will be required to travel and use own vehicle (Employer-paid mileage). Valid B.C. Driver’s license If you meet these requirements and are interested in this opportunity, we would like to hear from you! Please submit a resume and cover letter to jobs@orl.bc.ca outlining how your skills can be applied to a library setting. We thank all applicants for their interest in our organization; however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted. Compensation $120,000 to $140,000 per year Closes: 19 June, 2024 Okanagan Regional Library Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
